node.text:
Round 5 of the @ara_rally championship was probably the deepest field of top cars ever for an american rally. This stage was unique because it was the first time any of us had ever seen it and the top 5 cars finished within 2.5 seconds. This isn’t uncommon for everyone to be within about a tenth of a second a mile on repeat stages because we have either driven it in years past or can find @gopro footage of someone at speed. After we make our notes at a rally @rhianongelsomino and I (all of the top drivers) do a lot of “homework” to double check our notes against in car from our previous years or people who were fastest on that stage to overlay footage to see where we can pick up time by driving faster and where we can slow down to avoid big risk. Of course there are differences in road conditions from year to year and every car handles differently but if you want to be competitive these days you have to put in hundreds of hours of video review.. New stages are cool because it’s like walking a moto track and then your first lap of practice, without having seen anyone on the track before, is the only one that counts. When we run this stage next year, we will all pick up at least 2 seconds on this stage by watching video. It was one of my worst stages of the rally as far as mistakes and lifts where I could have been flat out, but that’s the beauty of new stages.. it’s an even playing field.
@subarumotorsportsusa @yokohamatire @kmcwheels @nitrocircus @thehoonigans @kuhl @alpinestars @rhianongelsomino

node.text:
Spent the week here in Minnesota building the track for round two of the championship. Amazing working with @andrewcarlson15 and crew. The track has so much elevation change, huge banks and zer-gravity drops. It’s windy and going to race really well. Almost no dust and great dirt here but we are intentionally not watering a few of the corners to see if the swept line could be a potential solution for other tracks where the soil blue grooves right away. Happy to get some laps on the CanAm to confirm the jumps are super smooth and will be easy on the cars.
@scott_speed @nitrocircus @yokohamatire @redbullmotorsports

node.text: @matt_crafton and his family came over to drive the @canamoffroad vehicles around the house. Good family fun. #igotfullcoverage 😂 Thanks for all the help and filming a few clips for us @nitrorednekhubert .. Crafton was the first one in a year to break one of these which is very impressive. Can Am’s are are tough as they come. Also, to be fair to Matt, it was pretty bent from @conordaly22 last cartwheel which I’m sure contributed 🤔🤦👍

Top choices so far
-Tea Party - Twisted Tea LSB - Twisted Viper. I will be throttling with @jim_york at the wheel for next years @p1offshore pro stock V championship. We are running this weekend at Morehead City as a warm up for the World championships in November. #tworookiesoneboat #whenindoubtthrottleout #bestworstideaever 
@pit_viper @lillysportboats66 @alpinestars @nitrocircus @bellhelmets #redbullfamily

Every wonder what it feels like to go into turn one at @crandonoffroad with a 900hp truck at 100mph 12 wide? Check out my forehead camera (thanks @tannerfoust for letting me use that) from lap 1.
@redbull @yokohamatire @carlsonmoto @andrewcarlson15 @kmcwheels @pit_viper @alpinestars @bellhelmets link in bio for full video

node.text: Never been happier with 7th. Had a lot of fun and that puts me on the front row for tomorrow’s world championship. @crandonoffroad @yokohamatire @redbullmotorsports @nitrocircus @brycemenzies7 @alpinestars @kmcwheels @carlsonmoto dream come true to run a pro-4. Getting to race so many legends. #funtimes❤️ thank you for the opportunity @niknamm
